          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 5g Ti metal powder (>99.9%) was pressed at",
                "10t/cm2 and disk (2cm in diam., 0.5 cm - thick) was",
                "obtained. Fifteen such samples, each sandwiched",
                "between pairs of aluminum  sheets (2 cm diam. x0.1cm),",
                "were suspended from a graduated ring."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2ZZZGEL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A 3 mg/cm2 T-Ti target was used. The target",
                " was backed by a 4 cm diameter silver sheet of 0.3 mm",
                " thickness, fixed in an aluminum  tube of 1 mm wall",
                " thickness. The silver sheet was cooled by a thin",
                " water film."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "  Neutron flux density is given as MISC in Subent 002."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The samples were activated in different",
                " angular positions with respect to the beam direction.",
                " In this way the neutron energy variation with angle",
                " from the source reaction could be used for the exci-",
                " tation function measurement."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma-ray spectroscopy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 35 cm**3 Ge(Li) detector to measure sample",
                " activity induced."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "1-H-1(N,EL)1-H-1,,DA",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "1-H-1(N,EL)1-H-1,,DA",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "1-H-1(N,EL)1-H-1",
                        "target": "1-H-1",
                        "projectile": "N",
                        "process": "EL",
                        "product": "1-H-1",
                        "quantity": ",DA",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A proton recoil telescope,",
                " positioned at an angle of 16 degrees relative to the",
                " deuteron beam direction and at a source to radiator",
                " distance of 80 cm, was used for the absolute fluence",
                " determination. The fluence at other angles was deter-",
                " mined by using the known angular distribution of the",
                " source reaction. The fluence rates averaged over the",
                " sample volumes were in the range 0.6 to 1.8E+6",
                " neutrons/cm**2/sec."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "13-AL-27(N,A)11-NA-24,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "13-AL-27(N,A)11-NA-24,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "13-AL-27(N,A)11-NA-24",
                        "target": "13-AL-27",
                        "projectile": "N",
                        "process": "A",
                        "product": "11-NA-24",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " In addition, the activities from the 13-Al-27(N,A)-",
                " reaction in the aluminum  foils were detected with",
                " gamma-ray spectroscopy using the same equipment as",
                " for the activity measurements for the molybdenum",
                " sheets."
              ]
            }
          ],
